## Diagnosis
Pod is marked as `Ready: False` because the Readiness probe (HTTP GET /healthz) is failing with status code 503 (service unavailable). The backend-w-df92 workload is still starting up and depends on an external DB that is not ready yet.

## Fix Plan
Set a reasonable timeout for the Readiness probe and increase the interval so it doesn't constantly check while the backend is starting up.

## Remediation
Change the Readiness probe configuration to wait longer before marking the pod as ready.

## Verification
Verify the fix by checking the pod's readiness and waiting for it to become ready.

## Rollback Guidance
If the fix causes issues, roll back to the previous configuration and investigate further.

### Actions
```shell
# Update the deployment with the new probe configuration
kubectl patch deployment backend-w-df92 -p '{
  "spec": {
    "template": {
      "spec": {
        "containers": [
          {
            "name": "server",
            "readinessProbe": {
              "httpGet": {
                "path": "/healthz",
                "port": 8080
              },
              "initialDelaySeconds": 10,
              "periodSeconds": 10,
              "timeoutSeconds": 5,
              "failureThreshold": 3
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  }
}'

# Verify the update
kubectl get pod backend-w-df92-pod-ldg1 -o yaml | grep readinessProbe
```

### Verification Steps
```shell
# Check the pod's readiness
kubectl get pod backend-w-df92-pod-ldg1 -o jsonpath='{.status.conditions[?(@.type=="Ready")].status}'

# Wait until the pod becomes ready
until kubectl get pod

